The paper deals with approximation algorithms for Steiner tree and forest problems in low dimensional spaces, which are classic topics in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves some analysis of the approximation ratio and runtime complexity, which suggests that it may also fit into cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
